ughout the Term 3. There is a minimum requirement of five meetings with individual supervisors in Term 3. In addition to supervisory meetings, students are required to attend course meetings with the convenor and the entire class; the dates for these meetings will be established prior to T3 commencement. </p><br />","hb_assessments":[{"delivery_variation":{"cl_id":"b64b61b3dbfd1c50eb6b147a3a961981","name":"Independent research - Standard (usually weekly or fortnightly)"},"assessments":[{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Thesis","assessment_type":{"label":"Report","value":"report"},"assessment_id":"1","weighting":"100","description":"<p>A thesis, which will range between 10,000-15,000 words, no more than 15,000 words, and will include pretinent ethics documentation. The thesis is marked by two people. One is your supervisor, and the other is another member of the full-time or part-time planning teaching staff or external supervisor.  All grades received are discussed in an assessment meeting by program staff. The examination process, as far as feasible, will be confined to the official UNSW Australia periods for marking and evaluation. All students will receive a report from each of their examiners summarising an appreciation of their work.</p>

<p> </p>
